               correspond to the soft (i.e. zero energy) modes of the elastic
               propagator that governs the redistribution of shear stress due to
               localized plastic events. Projections onto these soft modes also
               correspond to components of the displacement structure factor at
               the first nonzero wavevectors, in close analogy to PCA results
               for thermal phase transitions in conserved Ising spin systems.
