                 motion, crystal plasticity would show many features
                 different from those actually observed. The chapter
                 presents classical evidence and electron microscopic
                 evidence of work hardening. The general feature exposed
                 by the electron microscopic observations are that work
                 hardened dislocation structures is heterogeneous on a
                 mesoscopic scale. This set two new problems for the
