                 necessary to support design of hierarchically
                 structured materials, in some cases demanding atomic
                 scale resolution and in others cooperative behavior of
                 grains at scales 4--5 orders of magnitude larger. Some
                 recent progress in addressing key gaps in crystalline
                 plasticity models is discussed, including
                 distinguishing nucleation and growth processes, slip
