                 promising materials that can be integrated with other
                 2D materials, such as graphene and transition metal
                 dichalcogenides (TMDCs), for the next generation
                 microelectronic and other technologies. Although it is
                 by itself an insulator, it can well be tuned by several
                 strategies in terms of properties and functionalities,
                 such as by doping, substitution, functionalization and
                 hybridization, making 2D-hBN a truly versatile type of
                 functional materials for a wide range of applications.
                 In this review, the distinct structural characteristics
                 of 2D-hBN, doping- and defect-induced variations in
